                    },
                    "message": "Please come up with a single line summary under 52 chars followed by a line feed"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 15,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Patrick Williams",
                        "email": "patrick@stwcx.xyz",
                        "username": "williamspatrick"
                    },
                    "message": "We don't allow code in project layers.  What did you have in mind here."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 15,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "DelphineCCChiu",
                        "email": "Delphine_CC_Chiu@wiwynn.com",
                        "username": "DelphineCCChiu"
                    },
                    "message": "Hi Patrick\n\nThere is a function called isHostRunning for BMC to check host current state after BMC reboot.\n\nHowever, every project may use different ways to check host current state, like CPLD, GPIO, ...etc.\n\nIn that case, each project could implement their method in project layers.\n\nSo if we couldn't allow code in project layers, do you have any suggestions for this feature?"
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 15,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Geissler",
                        "email": "geissonator@yahoo.com",
                        "username": "geissonator"
                    },
                    "message": "Someone else needed it via GPIO so they created https://github.com/openbmc/phosphor-state-manager/tree/master/host_condition_gpio."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/COMMIT_MSG",
                    "line": 15,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "DelphineCCChiu",
                        "email": "Delphine_CC_Chiu@wiwynn.com",
                        "username": "DelphineCCChiu"
                    },
                    "message": "We will survey about it."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "Andrew Geissler",
                        "email": "geissonator@yahoo.com",
                        "username": "geissonator"
                    },
                    "message": "Overall the design within host-check is generic, it looks for \"something\" to implement the firmware running interface. If it doesn't find it, it doesn't do anything, if it does find it, it reads it. If you have a different way of doing this logic, just have it implement it under that interface. If you don't want it, don't implement it on your system.\n\nAs noted earlier, please take a look at the GPIO implementation in state-manager. Adding a -1 to this review until we get that investigation done."
                },
                {
                    "file": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
                    "line": 0,
                    "reviewer": {
                        "name": "DelphineCCChiu",
                        "email": "Delphine_CC_Chiu@wiwynn.com",
                        "username": "DelphineCCChiu"
                    },
                    "message": "We have other solution for this."
                }
